<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="113" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="113">Culture characteristics.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="14" pageNumber="113">Colonies on PDA attaining 12 mm diameter within 21 days at 25 °C under natural light, velvety, centrally raised, irregular to circular in shape, greenish grey and mixed with milky white mycelium at the edge of a colony, the reverse dull green or grey olivaceous.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
